	(text "IMPORTANT the flow of signal is as follows \n1) Connectors\n2) Current sensor(If EV), else Power supply GLV\n3) Implausibility_Plausibility Check, SCS Check\n4) Root\n5) Reset System \n6) Relay\n7) Back to connectors"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 193.294 28.194 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "147a9cad-3cb9-4d89-924d-45a023686885")
	)
	(text "PWR_RST only works for a short 200ms duration of the power\ncycle(>=500ms required for S = 1), hence no way of S and R \nbecoming 1 at through PWR_RST.\n\nSimilarily, only if implausibility is removed can 10s\nPlausibity give a High\n\nOnly for Reset Signal, it can happen, though, pushing the \nreset signal also resets the capacitor of the 500ms. "
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 195.834 128.778 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "32b87502-f46e-43bb-aeb0-463003004ee4")
	)
	(text "When Q is 0 and SCS check is 1, \n(SCS check bar is 0)then Relay should \nbe turned on"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 112.776 113.792 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "48398c00-3972-4fc1-9fec-0203d7bec230")
	)
	(text "Mounting Holes\n"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 143.256 169.672 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.254)
				(bold yes)
			)
		)
		(uuid "4a775f3d-5f9e-4157-9044-549320d35531")
	)
	(text "How the reset system\nWorks is by giving a short duration high \npulse, making R = 1 and assuming S = 0,\nmakes Q = 0."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 191.77 143.51 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
		)
		(uuid "7ca2f334-6644-4971-b9ab-5a1d3a0f45e2")
	)
